 Unfortunately, I can't create a direct overlay of symbols ⦿ and ⨉ in standard LaTeX code. However, I can suggest a few approaches:

1. Using the `\stackrel` command:
```latex
\stackrel{\mathsmaller{\times}}{\bigcirc}
```

2. Using `\overset`:
```latex
\overset{\mathsmaller{\times}}{\bigcirc}
```

3. Using TikZ for precise positioning:
```latex
\usepackage{tikz}
\newcommand{\blobx}{
  \begin{tikzpicture}[baseline]
    \node (a) {$\bigcirc$};
    \node at (a.center) {$\times$};
  \end{tikzpicture}
}
```

4. Creating a custom symbol with `\ooalign`:
```latex
\newcommand{\blobx}{%
  \mathord{\ooalign{\hfil$\bigcirc$\hfil\cr\hfil$\times$\hfil}}%
}
```

The `\ooalign` approach (#4) is probably the simplest if you want to use it inline without additional packages.

